1932;;Love in High Gear;;American;;Frank R. Strayer;;Alberta Vaughn, Tyrell Davis;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Love_in_High_Gear;;Ronald and Betty plan to elope, but are overheard by a jewel thief who has just stolen a pearl necklace from the wedding Ronald and Betty were attending. The jewel thief plans to use the situation to his advantage and a mad chase ensues towards the end of the film.[2][3]